<HEADLINE>
FT  10 FEB 94 / Trading standards move opposed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Welsh district councils are resisting attempts to set up large trading
standards authorities once local government in Wales is reorganised.
Trading standards officers believe businesses would face fragmented and
inconsistent regulation if the service were devolved to the 21 councils that
will replace the current eight Welsh councils. An amendment to create three
new trading standards authorities for Wales has been tabled in the Lords by
the Lord Elton (Conservative).
But the Council of Welsh Districts said yesterday: 'Such a move would mean
another blow to local democracy. The trading standards service is no more
complex and demanding than environmental health, a function which district
councils have carried out without complaint for many years.'
</TEXT>
