</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Engineering, a magazine founded in 1866, is closing because of continuing
losses.
The Design Council, which owns and publishes the magazine, said yesterday
that the February issue would be the last.
The publication, which had a circulation of 23,000 in 1992, was sent mainly
to those involved in engineering design and senior management in relatively
smaller companies. The magazine has found it difficult to win enough
advertising.
