<HEADLINE>
FT  10 FEB 94 / ITV in row over football timings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The ITV companies plan to seek an injunction against the Football League
over the timing of the broadcast of Coca Cola Cup semi-finals this month,
Raymond Snoddy writes.
The row has arisen because of rules adopted by Uefa, the Union of European
Football Associations, which try to ban live televised games between noon
and 4pm at weekends in order to protect attendances.
Because of opposition by the Scottish Football Association, the Football
League has been insisting that either the semi-finals are not shown in
Scotland or the kick-off is delayed until 4pm. Broadcasters have decided not
to challenge the Football League on this Sunday's semi-final between
Manchester United and Sheffield Wednesday when the kick-off will be delayed
to 4pm.
