</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WALLER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Degussa, the Frankfurt-based metals and chemicals group which has recently
completed the bulk of a rationalisation programme, yesterday reported group
earnings up 25 per cent for the three months to December. It predicted
further gains for the rest of the financial year to September.
First-quarter pre-tax profits rose by a quarter to DM60m (Dollars 35.3bn) on
turnover up 5 per cent to DM3.5bn, due mainly to a large increase in
earnings from the chemicals division which benefited from rationalisation
and improved demand.
KWU, the power-generation and distribution arm of the Siemens electronics
and electricals group, increased turnover by 32 per cent to DM8.7bn in the
year to September.
