</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Scandinavian Airlines System (SAS) is near to finalising a deal to sell its
42 per cent stake in LanChile, Chile's leading airline. The shares could
change hands for around Dollars 19m.
SAS said the stake was no longer strategically important following the
collapse of its plans to merge with Swissair, Austrian Airlines and KLM
Royal Dutch Airlines in the so-called Alcazar project. It stopped flying to
South America in January 1992.
