<HEADLINE>
FT  09 FEB 94 / International Company News: German company takes 25 per cent
share in Polish brewery
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Brau und Brunen, a leading German brewing and soft drink company, has taken
a 25 per cent share in Okocim, a listed Polish brewery with about 8 per cent
market share and a high profile brand name, writes Christopher Bobinski in
Warsaw.
Okocim was told by Brau and Brunen of the share purchase last week. The news
surprised the industry which has seen the government barring foreign
investors from brewing privatisations.
Changes in Poland's securities laws which come into force next week bring
the point at which share purchases have to be referred to the securities
commission and the anti-monopoly board down from 33 per cent to 25 per cent.
A purchase of 33 per cent would trigger a mandatory bid for Okocim's
remaining equity.
However, Brau and Brunen has said it did not intend to increase its share
above the 25 per cent which cost the German company an estimated Dollars
20m.
</TEXT>
