FT  09 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Utility Cable starts trading
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Pounds 8.75m cash and paper reverse takeover of the JP Fitzpatrick
companies by Baillie Gifford Technology, the shell investment trust, was
approved yesterday at an egm. A change of name, to Utility Cable, became
effective on Monday.
The meeting also agreed the placing, rights issue, subscription agreement
and issue of management warrants announced on January 14.
The admission of the 1p ordinary shares and warrants to the Official List
has become effective and dealings began yesterday.
