FT  09 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Apollo Metals faces 'short-term pain'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Albert Hargreaves, chairman of Apollo Metals, told the annual meeting
that the balance sheet remained strong, stocks and debtors were under
control, and gearing was relatively low.
However, he saw no reason to change the view he expressed in his annual
statement that the company may have to experience further short-term pain in
order to achieve its longer-term strategic goals.
