FT  09 FEB 94 / Long-term outlook improving
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GRAHAM BOWLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The longer leading index of UK economic activity has begun to rise once
more, pointing to a favourable long-term outlook for the economy, Graham
Bowley writes.
The rise was revealed in figures published yesterday by the Central
Statistical Office.
Increases in business optimism and the rise in house-building starts in the
final quarter of last year boosted the index, which is supposed to signal
turning points in economic activity about 13 months in advance.
The shorter leading index, which indicates turning points in activity five
months in advance, and the coincident index, which tracks the business
cycle, both continued to rise, providing further evidence of the favourable
short-term outlook.
